.TH "LIGHTNING-CHANNEL-HTLC-COUNT" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-channel-htlc-count \- count in-flight HTLCs per channel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning channel-htlc-count
.RI [ channel_id ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Reports the number of in-flight HTLCs for each channel, split into
.B offered
(outbound) and
.B received
(inbound) counts.
Without
.IR channel_id ,
reports all channels.
Returns an empty array if the daemon is unreachable.
.PP
Output:
.nf
[{channel_id, peer_id, htlc_count, offered, received}]
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-node-htlc-list (1),
.BR lightning-channel-balance (1)
